==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sorrento work
<hw>Sor"ren"to work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Ornamental work, mostly
carved in olivewood, decorated with inlay, made at or near Sorrento,
Italy. Hence, more rarely, jig-saw work and the like done
anywhere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorrily</ent>⟦br⟧
